lead_paragraph: Eighteen-year-old Renato Sanches will become the youngest player to start for Portugal in a major tournament after coach Fernando Santos made two changes for the Euro 2016 quarter-final against Poland on Thursday.

headline.print_headline: Portugal Bring in Sanches, Eliseu, Poland Unchanged
